  "stage": {
    "id": "decentralization_cases",
    "stageNumber": 3,
    "title": "Real-World Decentralization Cases",
    "roomWidth": 20,
    "roomHeight": 15,
    "concepts": [
      {
        "id": "censorship_resistance",
        "title": "Censorship Resistance and Decentralization",
        "content": "## What is Censorship Resistance?\n\nOne of decentralization's core values is **Censorship Resistance**—the ability to resist when certain powers try to block information or services.\n\n## Case 1: Pirate Bay & Sci-Hub\n\n**Pirate Bay** (torrent search site) and **Sci-Hub** (free academic paper sharing) faced numerous legal attacks.\n\n- Only small groups managing domains faced legal risk\n- Original data remained decentralized\n- Even when domains were blocked, operations continued via mirror sites\n\n## Case 2: BitTorrent\n\nBitTorrent demonstrates even stronger censorship resistance:\n\n- Anyone can join or leave file maintenance at any time\n- No central server means \"no server to take down\"\n- Popular files are shared by thousands simultaneously\n\n## DAO's Censorship Resistance\n\nWhat DAOs aim for is not \"permanently evading censorship.\"\n\n> It's about **maintaining organizational stability under uncertainty and interference**.\n\nOnce smart contracts are deployed on blockchain:\n- Continue operating even if dev team disappears\n- Accessible from other countries even if one country bans it\n- Cannot shut down servers (there are none)",
        "position": {
          "x": 5,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "kleros_case",
        "title": "Kleros Decentralized Court Case Study",
        "content": "## What is Kleros?\n\n**Kleros** is a Paris, France-based decentralized dispute resolution platform. Instead of traditional courts' slow and expensive procedures, it provides fast and cheap blockchain-based arbitration.\n\n## How It Works\n\n1. **Dispute arises**: Two parties cannot agree\n2. **Juror selection**: **3,000 jurors randomly selected** from PNK token stakers in relevant category\n3. **Evidence review**: Jurors don't know each other, review evidence within 3 days\n4. **Voting**: Each votes according to their judgment\n5. **Execution**: Compensation automatically paid via smart contract two days later\n\n## Trustworthy Fairness\n\nWhen a DAO's main concern is not resisting the state but **performing some state functions (especially infrastructure management)**, decentralization becomes the **basis for fairness**.\n\n- No specific person can manipulate results\n- Random selection prevents collusion\n- All processes transparently recorded\n\n## Limitation: Case #1170 Controversy\n\nHowever, Kleros has limitations. In **Case #1170**, allegations arose that insiders mobilized large amounts of PNK tokens to guide decisions in their desired direction.\n\nTo address this:\n- Further distribution of token supply\n- Introduction of non-token governance elements\n\nwere suggested as needed.",
        "position": {
          "x": 9,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "dao_types_overview",
        "title": "15 Application Areas of DAOs",
        "content": "## World Being Transformed by DAOs\n\nAragon Blog's 2021 \"15 Ways the World is Being Transformed by DAOs\" summarized the various areas where DAOs are being applied.\n\n### 1. Developer Collectives\n\n- **BadgerDAO**: Brings Bitcoin to DeFi, develops synthetic BTC tracking tools\n- **Gitcoin**: Developer ecosystem for building decentralized web, distributed $22.8M\n- **API3**: Multi-chain network solving blockchain oracle problems\n\n### 2. Worker Collectives\n\n- **Raid Guild**, **dOrg**: Web3-focused design/development agencies\n- Modern revival of medieval guilds\n- Enables global worker coordination\n\n### 3. Art Collectives\n\n- **PleasrDAO**: Started as Telegram group, bought NFT for 310 ETH ($525,000)\n- Holds the most iconic NFTs in crypto history\n\n### 4. Metaverse / Virtual Worlds\n\n- **Decentraland**: \"Fully decentralized metaverse\"\n- Destroyed founding smart contract private keys\n- $MANA token for security council, dev grants, LAND policy voting\n\n### 5. Asset Management & Venture Capital\n\n- **BitDAO** (now Mantle): Raised $230M → Pivoted to L2 network\n- **Metacartel Ventures**: Focused on distributed systems and DeFi investment\n\n### Other Areas\n\nInsurance, trusts, project fundraising, fan ownership, real estate, media, politics, etc.",
        "position": {
          "x": 13,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      }
    ],
